description.narrative: Country programmes are efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality programming standards in achieving results for children., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Policy, Guidance And Technical Support For Country Programming And Reporting, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By end of 2020, evidence generation and advocacy for evidence based policy decisions enhanced.

description.narrative: In 2019, the Program Strategy Notes in line with national, regional and global priorities were developed in consultation with stakeholders. The HACT risk assurance plan was closely monitored with 100 per cent of HACT programme monitoring visits and spot checks achieved. All UNICEF staff and 100% of the targeted implementing partners (10 CSO/NGO partners & government Ministries) were trained on prevention of sexual exploitation and abuse of authority and tools for monitoring are in place. UNICEF Eswatini is actively engaged in the development of United Nations Sustainable Development Cooperation Framework (UNSDCF) ensuring that issues of children are highlighted. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:19/12/2019
